main event: A witness reported seeing a bright yellow and blue oblong object in Memphis, Tennessee on January 5 or 8, 1969.
interesting points: The object was seen for a length of 1-2 minutes and appeared to be approximately 1 mile away., The object changed course and gradually descended out of the field of vision., The witnessing occurred in an urban setting., The phenomenon was described as self-luminous and resembling the size and appearance of a full moon., No photographs or physical evidence were collected to document the sighting.
sighted object: a yellow and blue oblong object
witness description: The witness reported that they were not with anyone else at the time of the sighting.
